At last, an internal light. There’s so much wonderful stuff going on in this film but I got absurdly moved by the idea of choosing to transform oneself from a witness to the world to an active part of it. As someone who used to be tremendously anxious and depressed, I remember how I felt so dead inside, floating from thing to thing, carried along by the current of life.
